Class KLDivergence

  • java.lang.Object
    • bayes.information.KLDivergence

  • public class KLDivergence
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used to calculate the Kullback-Leibler Divergence between two DataSets given an attribute.

      • divergence

        public static java.lang.Double divergence(DataSet dataP,
                          DataSet dataQ,
                          Attribute a,
                          Attribute b)
        Calculates the joint Kullback-Leibler Divergence of the given attribute list between the two DataSets. Extremely vulnerable to race conditions. Do not run in parallel.
        Parameters:
        dataP - first DataSet
        dataQ - second DataSet
        attrs - attributes being measured
        Returns:
        the divergence
